<p itemprop="description">An infrastructure operations engineer maintains and monitors production infrastructure systems, ensuring optimal performance, availability, and reliability. They support day-to-day operations and respond to infrastructure incidents.</p>

<section class="role-details">
    <h2>Typical responsibilities</h2>
    <ul>
        <li itemprop="responsibility">Monitor and maintain production infrastructure systems</li>
        <li itemprop="responsibility">Respond to infrastructure incidents and performance issues</li>
        <li itemprop="responsibility">Perform routine maintenance and system updates</li>
        <li itemprop="responsibility">Implement monitoring and alerting for infrastructure components</li>
        <li itemprop="responsibility">Support capacity planning and performance optimization</li>
        <li itemprop="responsibility">Maintain infrastructure documentation and procedures</li>
        <li itemprop="responsibility">Collaborate with infrastructure engineers on system improvements</li>
    </ul>
</section>

